Name: passwordField

Type: property

Syntax: set the passwordField of field to {true | false}

Summary:
Specifies whether a field displays its contents as bullet characters to
conceal sensitive input such as a password.

Associations: field

Introduced: 1.0.0

OS: mac, windows, linux

Platforms: desktop, server

Example:
set the passwordField of field "Password" to true

Example:
set the passwordField of field "Confirm Password" to true

Example:
set the passwordField of field "Password" to false -- show text again

Value:
The <passwordField> of a <field> is true or false. By default, the
<passwordField> of a newly created <field> is false.

Description:
Use the <passwordField> property to mask sensitive text entry. When
<passwordField> is true, every character in the field is displayed as a
bullet character (•) regardless of what the user has typed. The actual
text stored in the field is never altered — scripts that read the
<text> property always receive the real content.

This property only affects rendering. It does not encrypt or otherwise
protect the field's contents in memory or on disk. For secure storage
of credentials, use appropriate encryption techniques in addition to
this property.

Setting <passwordField> to true on a field that already contains text
will immediately redraw that text as bullets. Setting it back to false
reveals the text again.

References: text (property), password (property), field (object),
stack (object)

Tags: ui

